column1: Will the month-over-month percentage change in Turkey's consumer price index reach or exceed 3.5% in both January 2023 and February 2023?

column6: January 2023 was 6.65% and 4.25% on average in 2022
Over the past months the average change in month-to-month inflation was 1.1835%. So in order to get inflation below 3,5% the difference to the average would have to be 1,716621253 times.
From 1.18% in December to 6.65% in January.
CPI has been below 3.5% since November 2022.
1.18% in Dec 2022, the January report might end this Q
